<p>Basic, if you are using someone else&#8217;s wireless connection, then you are always at risk because you&#8217;re on the same network as they are. There are too many ways for them to access your computer to write about here, but it&#8217;s rare unless that person is computer savvy. </p>
<p>Mary &#8211; What do you mean by tracking you? Are you talking about tracking your Internet activity? That is possible if they were able to use your computer. I would not worry about their computer running, that might be something else. To snoop on someone&#8217;s searches, they need to have software installed on YOUR computer, so make sure it&#8217;s locked when you are not around.</p>
